Rating: 4
Cider cream IS awesome. I have made this many times and recommend the following shortcut: cut the squash in half, scrape out the seeds, and roast upside down at 400 just until you can poke a toothpick through the squash. Let it cool down and then you can pull the peel right off and drop the squash into the pan (kind of mash it with a big spoon as you go). This saves all the peeling and chopping, which not only takes forever but leaves that icky raw squash coating on your hands.

