Rating: 4
I have made this soup quite a few times with a few alterations. First, make it a faster (but more expensive) process with pre-cut and peeled squash. If you don't use the pre-cut, remember that when you weigh a squash you are also weighing the parts you discard when peeled (this is why some people may have called it an "apple soup"). Second, I make it vegetarian style. Why kill a chicken, when veggie stock is just as tasty? Third, use the white and pale green parts of 3 leeks, not 2. Last, adding any type of cream to this soup cancels out the other flavors of the soup. And we're in a recession, less is more , eh? Instead, I roast a few pumpkin seeds as edible garnish to give to soup added nutrition and flavor.

