This is a wonderful addition to our Thanksgiving feast. It is much, much easier to split the squash in half, rub the cut side with olive oil, salt and pepper and roast cut side down until soft. The skin will pull right off and the soft squash can then be added right to the soup pot. Much better than peeling and cutting raw squash and the roasted flavor adds depth.

