Delicious - a complex and lovely flavor. I used fresh sage & lemon thyme from the garden - the usual equivalent of 3 times the dried amount. I roasted the squash first, so it would be easy to peel and cut up (Cut in quarters, roasted face down in a pan at 300F for 1 hour, peeled, cut in 1/2" chunks). Then, I added it to the sauteed leeks, carrots, celery and continued the recipe. Used a fresh cider, needed more than was called for of the reduced cider to give the cider cream the proper punch. Will ABSOLUTELY make again - next time for my winter soup party.

