Rating: 4
I made this for a holiday open house party. It was a big hit. I felt that the thyme was too strong but all of my guests liked it. I added a 1/4 t of nutmeg, 1/8 t cayenne, and one half of a large onion. I omitted the apple juice entirely and I used a bit more squash than the recipe calls for. To adapt this for the crock pot, which is the perfect way to serve this soup and keep it warm for a cocktail party, I pre-baked the squash. Meanwhile, I sauted all the other vegetables and the spices. I then combined the cooked squash, and the vegetables, and the broth in the crock pot and cooked for 5 hrs on high. I pureed it with my "boat motor", adding the cream.

