Rating: 4
What a wonderful soup. I don't understand the negative reviews. I have made this soup numerous times all with great success and raves from everyone who has tried it. I strongly agree in roasting the squash beforehand and add during the puree process (not before or you will cook all the flavor out of the squash). I also substituted creme fraiche in place of sour cream. I also added 1/2 granny smith apple, scant 1/2 teaspoon honey to the cider to infuse more flavor (let sit 10 minutes). Don't add too much cider cream to the soup!!! Also, the soup does not need the addtion of cream it's texture is perfect without it.

