Rating: 3
I was looking for a recipe because my grocery had squash on sale, 4-lbs. for a dollar! Lucky me, I found one more recipe for my "Delicious Dishes" file! My modifications: I roasted halved and seeded squash first in a 350-degree oven until tender (45 min.) and added the cooled, scooped out, cooked squash to the other veggies after they were tender. Believe it or not, I skipped the cream and added some milk instead. Gotta watch that waist line! Next time, I will add less sour cream to the cider reduction to intensify the apple flavor, but that's just a tweek to an excellent recipe. Do yourself a favor and try this one.

